# E2E Browser (`e2e/browser/`)

## Definition

- Full UI flow through the browser to the backend (Playwright).
- Specs: `e2e/browser/*.spec.js`; shared helpers: `e2e/browser/testHelpers.js`, `globalSetup.js`, `globalHooks.js`.

## Running

- From repo root: `npm run e2e` (runs port release / DB reset per project script when configured).
- If ports 8080 / 5173 are in use or running manually: `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/release-e2e-ports.ps1` first (see `workflow.mdc`).

## Implementation

- ASCII only in spec and helper source.
- Follow patterns in existing specs; for new coverage, see [.cursor/skills/text-idle-add-e2e-test/SKILL.md](.cursor/skills/text-idle-add-e2e-test/SKILL.md).

## Doc sync

- New or changed user flows: update specs **and** the artifacts listed in **Doc and Test Sync** (`workflow.mdc`) in the **same change**. E2E must not be the only updated surface while design docs or requirements examples stay stale.
